Roll Hall of Fame, Mozart und Graz, dem Genre HipHop, der Philharmonie und dem Jüdischen Museum in Berlin. Untersucht werden die Mechanismen ihrer Konstruktion, Beständigkeit und Beweglichkeit, die abhängig sind von individueller Erinnerung sowie institutionellen und gesellschaftspolitischen Kontexten. Inwiefern Musik, um nicht in Vergessenheit zu geraten, der medialen Verankerung und materiellen Verortung bedarf, wird in diesem Buch erkenntnisreich dargestellt.  aWhy do we remember certain music from the past and attribute meaning to it, while other protagonists from the history of music slip into obscurity? Armed with this question, the author embarks upon a journey to sites of memory in music, visiting Beethoven's Ninth Symphony, the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame, Mozart and Graz, the genre of hip hop, the philharmonic and the Jewish Museum in Berlin.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aErinnerungskultur. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aMusikgeschichte. 4akulturelles Gedächtnis. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aCultural memory.  aculture of remembrance.  ahistory of music.  amedia studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1z978311076682008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831107675130 cprintz978311076379940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110767483zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110767483zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www